terrapeer.vui.j3dui.utils.blocks
Class FeedbackBlocks

java.lang.Object
  terrapeer.vui.j3dui.utils.blocks.FeedbackBlocks
public class FeedbackBlocks
extends java.lang.Object

These utilities are common building block utilities that were first introduced for the book's examples on "feedback".

Because these building blocks are rather specific in purpose they are included here as utilities instead of as general purpose building block classes in the framework core.

buildTargetSelectEnablers

public static final void buildTargetSelectEnablers(MultiShape targetMulti,
                                                   EnableTarget targetTrigger,
                                                   EnableTarget targetSingle,
                                                   EnableTarget targetDouble,
                                                   EnableTarget targetTriple)
Creates feedback enable triggers that enable target control elements (e.g. actuators for translation, rotation, scale) according to the selection state (single, double, triple) of the target's multi-shape feedback source. The target's feedback status will be updated accordingly through its status trigger.

Note that all triggers will be initialized "true" to permit initialization of enable targets. The final act of initialization must be to initialize the multishape target state, which in turn initializes the triggers and their enable targets.

Parameters:
targetMulti - Target's feedback source. Never null.
targetTrigger - Target's status trigger. Null if none.
targetSingle - Single-select enable target. Null if none.
targetDouble - Double-select enable target. Null if none.
targetTriple - Triple-select enable target. Null if none.

buildMultiLift

public static final MultiShape buildMultiLift(boolean pickable,
                                              double handleW,
                                              double handleH)
Creates a MultiAction handle for lifting a target object. The object is a flat arrow pointing up along the Y axis with the origin at its bottom center.

This object was intended to be two flat arrows at right angles but problems with Java 3D 1.1.2 transparent object overlap preclude this. As such, for practical use, this object must be made display facing.

Parameters:
pickable - If true the object will be pickable.
handleW - Width of the handle.
handleH - Height of the handle.
Returns:
New MultiShape object containing the decorations.

buildMultiFloorTarget

public static final MultiShape buildMultiFloorTarget(javax.media.j3d.Node target,
                                                     AffineGroup slide,
                                                     AffineGroup rotate,
                                                     AffineGroup lift,
                                                     AppView view,
                                                     double height)
Creates a set of MultiShape feedback decorations for a target object that is intended to be slid, rotated, and lifted over an X-Z floor plane. The decorations include tooltips, handles, and sound.

Parameters:
target - Target object to be centered, offset, and decorated. If the target is a FeedbackTarget it will also be connected as a feedback target.
slide - Affine group used to slide the target. The group will be connected into an internal group chain and therefore should be supplied as new. Null if none.
rotate - Affine group used to rotate the target. The group will be connected into an internal group chain and therefore should be supplied as new. Null if none.
lift - Affine group used to slide the target. The group will be connected into an internal target chain and therefore should be supplied as new. Null if none.
view - Host environment for the sound audio device. If null then no sound.
height - Height (+Y) of the target above its origin.
Returns:
New MultiShape proxy target.
